{"type":"compaction","id":"7bb691da","parentId":"88059eb2","timestamp":"2026-05-10T14:16:23.254Z","summary":"\n## Goal\n1. Fix cache display bug: footer shows \"Cache: 0%\" in Telegram but actual session status shows 93% cache hit\n2. User wants reply format to use \"GPT 5.5\" as model name (via [MODEL] placeholder)\n3. User wants RTK to show \"ใช้ตรวจผล\" in footer\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Every cron/job must have `deleteAfterRun: true` — no exceptions (HARD RULE)\n- Hermes-related tasks require explicit permission before touching\n- All replies must use Thai language\n- Keep replies short and direct\n- If doing multi-step/long-running work, provide brief progress updates\n- If need to wait for system/index/download/build: create cron/job with auto-notify and self-cleanup, no garbage left\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Deleted Hermes health check cron (b8685011-a78e-4b55-bbc7-6ce600baecf4) — user said they'll handle Hermes manually\n- [x] Added CRON/JOB HARD RULE to MEMORY.md: `deleteAfterRun: true` mandatory for all jobs\n- [x] Reverted AGENTS.md changes to keep `[MODEL]` placeholder and `RTK: ใช้ตรวจผล`\n- [x] Session_status confirms actual cache: `93% hit · 27k cached, 1.7k new` — cache IS working\n- [x] RTK is functional (confirmed via `rtk gain` showing 6.2% global savings)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Cache display bug in Telegram footer still shows \"0%\" while actual session cache is 93% hit\n- [ ] User says \"มันยังไม่เปลี่ยน\" (it still hasn't changed) — the footer 0% issue persists\n\n### Blocked\n- The Telegram footer consistently shows \"Cache: 0%\" despite session_status showing 93% cache hit — this is a display/rendering bug, not an actual cache problem\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Cron deleted**: User prefers to manually notify when Hermes dies rather than having automated health check that persists\n- **Format reverted**: User showed the correct format with `[GPT 5.5]` and `[สรุป]` — assistant should not have changed AGENTS.md without clear user request\n- **Cache is NOT broken**: session_status confirms 93% hit; only the Telegram footer display is wrong\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Investigate why Telegram footer shows \"Cache: 0%\" when session_status shows 93% — check if footer reads from different cache metric source\n2. The issue is likely in how the footer template fetches/calculates the cache percentage vs the session_status tool\n3. Check if there's a template or rendering issue in the OpenClaw Telegram channel output\n\n## Critical Context\n- Current footer format in AGENTS.md: `[Tokens: ระดับ | Cache: X% | RTK: ใช้ตรวจผล | Session: X%]`\n- Actual session data (from session_status): `Cache: 93% hit · 27k cached, 1.7k new`\n- The 0% is NOT the actual cache — actual cache is working at 93%\n- RTK working confirmed: `rtk gain` shows 1.9M input tokens, 115.8K tokens saved (6.2%)\n- Files at: `/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `IDENTITY.md`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user (robberzaz via Telegram) is complaining that the cache percentage in the footer always shows `0%` and never changes, despite the system cache actually working properly. They want it to display the real cache percentage.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant confirmed via `session_status` that actual cache is working (17% hit rate, 30k cached)\n- The footer format is defined in AGENTS.md: `[Tokens: ระดับ | Cache: X% | RTK: ใช้ตรวจผล | Session: X%]`\n- The assistant was investigating where the \"Cache: 0%\" value is generated by searching OpenClaw's dist files, config files, and session data\n- The assistant identified that the footer with `Cache: 0%` is manually written by the model (assistant) in replies, not auto-injected by OpenClaw\n- The assistant discovered that older session entries in the JSONL file show `cacheRead:0, cacheWrite:0` in their usage stats\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant is reading the session JSONL file to find historical cache stats and understand why the footer shows 0%. The retained suffix shows entries from the Telegram session (2c3e6a7a-3fb2-4bc2-8265-a5d8a6ebf93d.jsonl) where older messages have `cacheRead:0, cacheWrite:0, totalTokens:0` in their usage objects - suggesting at that time the cache wasn't being tracked or was zeroed.\n\n<read-files>\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json\n~/.openclaw/skills/rtk-integration/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/IDENTITY.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"6b9d48b7","tokensBefore":52965,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs","/home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json","~/.openclaw/skills/rtk-integration/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/AGENTS.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/IDENTITY.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/MEMORY.md"]},"fromHook":false}
